div.p:
               The Prince of Conde, being taken Prisoner by Charles the ninth of France;
and put to his choise, whether he would go to Mass, or be put to death, or
suffer perpetuall imprisonment? answered, The former I will never do by
Gods grace; as for the two latter, let the King do with me what he pleaseth;
for God, I assure my selfe, will turne all to the best.
